WEBVTT

00:00.313 --> 00:02.098
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:02.141 --> 00:03.403
the people are represented

00:03.447 --> 00:05.797
by two separate,
yet equally important groups:

00:05.840 --> 00:07.755
the police,
who investigate crime,

00:07.799 --> 00:10.715
and the district attorneys,
who prosecute the offenders.

00:10.758 --> 00:13.805
These are their stories.

00:13.848 --> 00:15.633
- We're trying to carve out
a middle ground--

00:15.676 --> 00:17.287
a place where these issues
can be discussed

00:17.330 --> 00:19.028
in a civil manner.
- Only if we agree with you.

00:19.071 --> 00:22.118
If we disagree, then we're
suddenly idiots or hicks.

00:22.161 --> 00:23.641
- That's not true.
- I see and hear it

00:23.684 --> 00:25.164
every day, Derek--

00:25.208 --> 00:27.993
liberals refusing to discuss
issues that really matter:

00:28.037 --> 00:29.864
economic issues,
geopolitical issues--

00:29.908 --> 00:32.737
as far as I can see, the only
thing you guys wanna talk about

00:32.780 --> 00:34.347
is identity politics;

00:34.391 --> 00:36.697
gender, race, sexual identity.

00:36.741 --> 00:38.395
I swear to God,
it's like you spend

00:38.438 --> 00:41.354
all your time and energy just
inventing ways to be offended.

00:41.398 --> 00:42.442
- But it's more complicated
than that.

00:42.486 --> 00:43.791
- No! No.

00:43.835 --> 00:45.532
See, there you go again,
pandering to us morons,

00:45.576 --> 00:47.491
'cause we can't
quite grasp the subtleties

00:47.534 --> 00:49.449
of the complex
liberal platform.

00:49.493 --> 00:51.103
- I just think we need
to talk about these issues

00:51.147 --> 00:52.887
in a serious, honest way.

00:52.931 --> 00:55.629
There's a middle road here,
a way to bridge the gap.

00:55.673 --> 00:57.544
We need to have
more conversations--

00:57.588 --> 00:59.503
- Do you believe the leaders
of the Democratic Party

00:59.546 --> 01:01.287
are involved
in the sexual exploitation

01:01.331 --> 01:02.636
of underage boys and girls?

01:02.680 --> 01:05.509
[dramatic music]

01:05.552 --> 01:07.337
- Are you really doing this?
- Doing what?

01:07.380 --> 01:09.121
- Talking about
this QAnon crap.

01:09.165 --> 01:10.862
You told me--

01:10.905 --> 01:12.951
you promised me
this would be a civil,

01:12.994 --> 01:14.909
constructive conversation,

01:14.953 --> 01:17.477
that we'd debate the issues.

01:18.870 --> 01:22.178
- You still haven't answered
the question, Mr. Hoyt.

01:22.221 --> 01:24.136
[tense, dramatic music]

01:24.180 --> 01:25.137
- Go to hell.

01:25.181 --> 01:29.707
♪

01:29.750 --> 01:30.969
[door clicks shut]

01:31.012 --> 01:32.666
- People can sit
in their basement apartment

01:32.710 --> 01:36.322
surrounded by cats and
pizza boxes and just spew hate.

01:36.366 --> 01:37.889
- Yeah, 'cause there
aren't any consequences.

01:37.932 --> 01:39.369
- You can't fight back either.

01:39.412 --> 01:41.632
You tweet back?
You're a troll.

01:41.675 --> 01:44.330
- Two weeks ago,
this idiot called me a racist,

01:44.374 --> 01:46.158
because I said
Jay-Z is overrated.

01:46.202 --> 01:47.768
Like, what?

01:47.812 --> 01:49.596
- Back in the day, if you
wanted to call out someone,

01:49.640 --> 01:51.468
you did it in person,
face-to-face.

01:51.511 --> 01:52.730
- And you just might get
your damn ass kicked too--

01:52.773 --> 01:55.689
[tires squeal and crash,
screaming]

01:55.733 --> 01:57.169
[line ringing]

01:57.213 --> 01:58.779
- 911.
What's your emergency?

01:58.823 --> 02:00.868
- I'm on the corner
of 29th and 10th.

02:00.912 --> 02:03.219
Someone just got hit by a bus.
- And what's his condition?

02:03.262 --> 02:05.134
- He's bleeding.
It's really bad.

02:05.177 --> 02:07.701
♪

02:07.745 --> 02:09.094
- [groans]

02:09.138 --> 02:11.009
♪

02:11.052 --> 02:13.707
- [indistinct shouting]
You all witnessed it.

02:13.751 --> 02:16.580
- Why are we here,
Officer Washington?

02:16.623 --> 02:18.190
- 'Cause it wasn't an accident.

02:18.234 --> 02:19.626
Two witnesses saw some dude

02:19.670 --> 02:21.759
push the DOA
in front of the bus.

02:21.802 --> 02:23.674
- These witnesses
get a good look at the guy?

02:23.717 --> 02:25.023
- No.

02:25.066 --> 02:27.939
He was wearing a facemask
and a dark winter hat.

02:27.982 --> 02:29.462
- What about the bus driver?

02:29.506 --> 02:32.291
- She didn't wanna talk.

02:32.335 --> 02:33.901
Said she's too upset.

02:35.468 --> 02:37.601
- Did he seem mentally ill?

02:37.644 --> 02:39.255
Did he say anything specific?

02:39.298 --> 02:40.647
- No,
he just rolled up on the dude

02:40.691 --> 02:42.258
and shoved him
into the street.

02:42.301 --> 02:44.738
- You got a good look at him.
Did you see his complexion?

02:44.782 --> 02:46.784
- Uh, he was white,

02:46.827 --> 02:48.133
maybe brown.

02:48.177 --> 02:49.308
I couldn't really tell,
'cause he was wearing

02:49.352 --> 02:51.528
a facemask
and a dark ski hat.

02:51.571 --> 02:53.399
- Okay.
What was his body type?

02:53.443 --> 02:56.402
Was he tall, or short,
heavyset, thin?

02:56.446 --> 02:58.709
- 5'10", but he definitely
wasn't skinny.

02:58.752 --> 03:00.841
More like beefy.

03:00.885 --> 03:02.278
- Thank you.

03:02.321 --> 03:03.714
What do you got?

03:03.757 --> 03:05.890
- Downloaded
the bus cam footage.

03:07.935 --> 03:09.023
- Wow.

03:09.067 --> 03:11.200
That's a lot of hate
behind that push.

03:11.243 --> 03:12.723
- Question is why?

03:12.766 --> 03:16.292
♪

03:16.335 --> 03:19.382
[dramatic music]

03:19.425 --> 03:26.563
♪

03:36.442 --> 03:43.580
♪

03:53.459 --> 04:00.597
♪

04:03.600 --> 04:07.299
- I have no idea why someone
would wanna kill Derek.

04:07.343 --> 04:09.345
It doesn't make sense.

04:09.388 --> 04:11.521
- Did you and Derek
have any problems?

04:11.564 --> 04:14.175
- No.
Everything was great.

04:14.219 --> 04:16.656
- Forgive me for asking,
it's just part of the process.

04:16.700 --> 04:19.877
Were either you or your husband
involved with anyone else?

04:19.920 --> 04:22.096
- No, nothing like that.

04:22.140 --> 04:25.709
- Did Derek gamble, drink?

04:25.752 --> 04:27.493
- Uh,

04:27.537 --> 04:29.278
maybe a glass of wine
here and there, but...

04:32.368 --> 04:34.848
He was a good person.

04:34.892 --> 04:39.418
He loved being a father,
a husband.

04:39.462 --> 04:41.551
He was going to run
for Congress too.

04:41.594 --> 04:44.205
He wanted to...

04:44.249 --> 04:46.556
give back,
make a difference.

04:48.384 --> 04:51.430
It sounds cliché,
but he really meant it.

04:51.474 --> 04:54.303
[indistinct chatter]

04:54.346 --> 04:55.956
I'll be there in a minute.

04:56.000 --> 04:57.349
Go play with Laura, okay?

04:57.393 --> 05:04.487
♪

05:07.664 --> 05:11.537
- Uh, if you can think
of anything else,

05:11.581 --> 05:13.234
would you give us a call?

05:13.278 --> 05:14.279
- Yeah.

05:14.323 --> 05:16.803
♪

05:16.847 --> 05:20.372
It might be nothing, but
Derek got into an argument

05:20.416 --> 05:23.636
with another man
a few weeks ago.

05:23.680 --> 05:26.726
We were having dinner, and...

05:26.770 --> 05:29.338
this guy started
yelling at him.

05:29.381 --> 05:31.557
It got really heated.

05:31.601 --> 05:34.081
- Do you remember what
they were arguing about?

05:34.125 --> 05:38.216
- No, he just kept calling
Derek a liar and a phony.

05:38.259 --> 05:40.087
Then Derek pushed him away.

05:40.131 --> 05:45.397
♪

05:45.441 --> 05:49.096
- Yeah, Derek and I got into it
pretty good that night.

05:49.140 --> 05:50.533
Wasn't a big deal, though.

05:50.576 --> 05:53.623
Just a couple of alpha dogs
barking at each other.

05:53.666 --> 05:56.887
- What were you two
barking about?

05:56.930 --> 05:59.455
- I tried to buy his firm,
but he sold it to someone else.

05:59.498 --> 06:01.021
Offered him 50% more
than I did.

06:01.065 --> 06:03.459
- You were pissed
that another company

06:03.502 --> 06:04.851
wanted to pay more money?

06:04.895 --> 06:06.070
- I was pissed
because he didn't give me

06:06.113 --> 06:07.419
a chance to counter.

06:07.463 --> 06:09.508
- Pissed enough to shove him
in front of a bus?

06:09.552 --> 06:10.901
- [scoffs]
Please.

06:10.944 --> 06:12.816
I loved Derek.
- I saw the video.

06:12.859 --> 06:15.035
I didn't see
a lot of love there.

06:15.079 --> 06:18.691
- What you saw was
two real men talking business--

06:18.735 --> 06:23.087
face-to-face, no lawyers,
no PR, no social media.

06:23.130 --> 06:25.568
Just a couple of grown-ass men
gettin' after it.

06:25.611 --> 06:30.050
- Unfortunately,
Derek is now dead.

06:30.094 --> 06:31.617
- And that sucks.

06:31.661 --> 06:34.011
Like I said,
he was a good dude.

06:34.054 --> 06:36.796
- Did you talk to or see him
after the altercation

06:36.840 --> 06:38.972
at the restaurant?
- Yeah, met him for coffee

06:39.016 --> 06:40.278
a few days ago.

06:40.321 --> 06:41.627
- Like a real man?

06:41.671 --> 06:44.021
- Pledged a million dollars
to his campaign too.

06:44.064 --> 06:46.458
- Hm.
- And that was the last time

06:46.502 --> 06:47.981
you saw him?
- Well, technically,

06:48.025 --> 06:49.896
the last time was
in front of his building.

06:49.940 --> 06:52.638
He shook my hand,
said thanks, and that was that.

06:52.682 --> 06:55.728
- Did he mention
anything unusual,

06:55.772 --> 06:57.077
maybe somebody harassing him?

06:57.121 --> 06:58.818
- There was this guy
following us.

06:58.862 --> 07:00.951
Looked like
he was taking photos too.

07:00.994 --> 07:02.692
- Do you remember
what he looked like?

07:02.735 --> 07:04.955
- White, about 50,

07:04.998 --> 07:06.783
average height.

07:06.826 --> 07:09.089
He was wearing a Phillies hat.

07:09.133 --> 07:12.136
[indistinct chatter,
phones ringing]

07:12.179 --> 07:13.746
[ominous music]

07:13.790 --> 07:15.618
- Think I got something.

07:15.661 --> 07:17.576
- What do you got?

07:17.620 --> 07:20.927
- Look at this guy
with the camera.

07:20.971 --> 07:23.495
- Can you zoom in,
get a better look at his face?

07:25.541 --> 07:26.890
- No,
that's the best I can do.

07:26.933 --> 07:29.240
- Take a look at that jacket.

07:29.283 --> 07:33.418
NYPD Fighting 19th Softball.

07:33.462 --> 07:35.333
- Guy's a cop.

07:35.376 --> 07:37.161
- Or a softball groupie.

07:37.204 --> 07:40.425
- Send that over to the 19th.
See if anyone recognizes him.

07:40.469 --> 07:45.125
♪

07:45.169 --> 07:46.518
- Yeah, that's me.

07:46.562 --> 07:49.478
I was followin' the guy
on the right, Derek Hoyt.

07:49.521 --> 07:51.001
- Why?

07:51.044 --> 07:53.264
- Got hired about a month ago
to find some dirt.

07:53.307 --> 07:56.093
But I came up empty.
Guy's squeaky clean.

07:56.136 --> 07:58.661
Then last week, they asked me
to give it another whirl.

07:58.704 --> 08:00.532
- What were they
hoping to find?

08:00.576 --> 08:02.447
- Don't know.
Didn't ask.

08:02.491 --> 08:03.840
Gotta pay the bills, bro.

08:03.883 --> 08:05.885
- Hell of a way to do it.

08:05.929 --> 08:08.975
- Do me a favor.
Don't judge.

08:09.019 --> 08:11.238
- During the course of your,
uh, investigation,

08:11.282 --> 08:13.806
did you happen
to find anything of concern?

08:13.850 --> 08:16.156
- No, nothing even close.

08:17.549 --> 08:19.159
- So who hired you?

08:19.203 --> 08:22.206
Who was looking for
all this dirt on Derek Hoyt?

08:26.079 --> 08:28.168
♪

08:28.212 --> 08:29.300
- That's so crazy.

08:29.343 --> 08:30.823
I just interviewed him
this morning.

08:30.867 --> 08:34.435
- Mm.
- So how can I help?

08:34.479 --> 08:37.961
- Well, you can start by, uh,
telling us why you hired

08:38.004 --> 08:40.833
a P.I. to dig up dirt
on Mr. Hoyt.

08:40.877 --> 08:43.009
- What's that got to do
with him gettin' hit by a bus?

08:43.053 --> 08:44.663
- I don't know, maybe nothin'.

08:44.707 --> 08:45.838
- We're trying to figure out

08:45.882 --> 08:47.884
why someone
would try to kill him.

08:49.059 --> 08:50.626
- I don't know.
I know he was planning

08:50.669 --> 08:52.192
on running for Congress,

08:52.236 --> 08:54.586
and that the power brokers
in the Democratic Party

08:54.630 --> 08:58.764
were talking about him like he
was the, uh, next big thing--

08:58.808 --> 09:02.028
AOC with some brains.
[chuckles]

09:02.072 --> 09:04.901
Uh, that was a joke.
Sorry.

09:04.944 --> 09:07.643
Didn't mean to offend
your left-wing sensibilities.

09:07.686 --> 09:10.384
- No, you didn't offend us.
It wasn't funny.

09:10.428 --> 09:12.256
- Oh, tough crowd.

09:12.299 --> 09:15.041
- More like impatient.
We're investigating a murder.

09:15.085 --> 09:17.043
- You're right, you're right.
I'm sorry.

09:17.087 --> 09:18.654
I'd heard some rumors
about Hoyt,

09:18.697 --> 09:21.047
so I hired a P.I. for him,
to look into him.

09:21.091 --> 09:23.180
I didn't want to publish
anything without confirmation.

09:23.223 --> 09:26.836
- Hm, because of your
journalistic integrity?

09:26.879 --> 09:28.577
- What kind of rumors?

09:28.620 --> 09:30.622
- I'd rather not comment
on that.

09:30.666 --> 09:31.841
You know, now that he's gone,

09:31.884 --> 09:34.278
there's no need
to besmirch the deceased.

09:34.321 --> 09:35.888
- Ha!
[laughs]

09:35.932 --> 09:37.281
- Yeah.
- Now, that's funny.

09:37.324 --> 09:40.066
You know, you pretending
to have ethical standards.

09:40.110 --> 09:42.895
Your whole mission is to
cultivate hate and mistrust.

09:42.939 --> 09:45.637
- I run a media business,
all right?

09:45.681 --> 09:47.291
I give the people
what they want--

09:47.334 --> 09:48.640
real people--

09:48.684 --> 09:51.600
real, honest, hardworking,
middle-class people

09:51.643 --> 09:53.340
who love this country

09:53.384 --> 09:55.473
who can't relate
to the rich, coastal elites

09:55.516 --> 09:58.911
who control the media
and the political narrative.

09:58.955 --> 10:01.522
Come on, you really think
some roofer from Akron

10:01.566 --> 10:02.828
with a mortgage and three kids

10:02.872 --> 10:05.352
gives a rat's ass
about somebody's pronoun?

10:05.396 --> 10:09.400
- So you...don't believe
liberals eat babies,

10:09.443 --> 10:11.924
or that Black people's
obsession with racism

10:11.968 --> 10:13.360
is destroying the country?

10:13.404 --> 10:15.624
- It doesn't matter
what I believe.

10:15.667 --> 10:17.669
It matters what sells.

10:17.713 --> 10:20.106
- And destroying Hoyt
would sell?

10:20.150 --> 10:23.632
- Yeah, destroying him
would've been a home run.

10:23.675 --> 10:24.720
But he's gone.

10:24.763 --> 10:25.982
So we'll just have to find

10:26.025 --> 10:28.114
another Democratic heartthrob
to lambaste.

10:28.158 --> 10:29.768
[chuckles]

10:29.812 --> 10:31.422
- So far,
we're coming up empty.

10:31.465 --> 10:33.424
Victim is a choir boy.

10:33.467 --> 10:35.208
No vices, no motives,

10:35.252 --> 10:37.080
even that right-wing prick,
Reed,

10:37.123 --> 10:38.472
can't dig up any dirt on him.

10:38.516 --> 10:40.431
- Yeah, could just be
a random act of violence--

10:40.474 --> 10:42.955
an emotionally unstable guy
acting on impulse.

10:42.999 --> 10:45.958
- Well, it's possible,
but keep digging

10:46.002 --> 10:47.351
into this Jordan Reed angle.

10:47.394 --> 10:49.135
He said there were
some rumors swirling,

10:49.179 --> 10:50.833
so let's find out
what they were.

10:50.876 --> 10:52.748
- Mm-hmm.
- Think I know!

10:52.791 --> 10:54.097
Computer Crimes
just did a deep dive

10:54.140 --> 10:56.012
on the victim's
electronic devices--

10:56.055 --> 10:57.317
found some deleted emails

10:57.361 --> 10:59.102
filled with
veiled death threats.

10:59.145 --> 11:01.582
"You're a gutless pig.
You deserve to die."

11:01.626 --> 11:02.801
- Know where they came from?

11:02.845 --> 11:05.021
- No, they were sent
from an untraceable app.

11:05.064 --> 11:06.979
Good news is,
if you want to call it that,

11:07.023 --> 11:09.982
pretty sure I know why
these guys are threatening him.

11:10.026 --> 11:12.245
Found this
on his deleted email folder.

11:12.289 --> 11:16.336
This young girl Hoyt's with
is definitely not his daughter.

11:16.380 --> 11:18.599
♪

11:18.643 --> 11:20.253
- So much for being
a choir boy.

11:20.297 --> 11:22.125
♪

11:23.953 --> 11:24.344
.

11:24.388 --> 11:26.825
- This doesn't make any sense.
Where'd you get these photos?

11:26.869 --> 11:28.871
- Off his computer.

11:28.914 --> 11:30.873
- There's no way Derek
would ever be involved.

11:30.916 --> 11:32.788
- No, well,
these are just photos, ma'am,

11:32.831 --> 11:35.791
we don't have any proof of
anything illegal at the moment.

11:35.834 --> 11:38.097
- We're just trying to ID
the young girls in the photos

11:38.141 --> 11:40.578
so we can contact
their parents.

11:40.621 --> 11:42.667
Sorry,
it's just the way it is.

11:42.711 --> 11:43.755
- Do you know these two girls?

11:46.279 --> 11:47.716
- I know her.

11:47.759 --> 11:49.413
She goes
to my daughter's school.

11:49.456 --> 11:52.111
[somber music]

11:52.155 --> 11:55.245
- It's a good thing this
sick son of a bitch is dead.

11:55.288 --> 11:56.507
- Mm.

11:56.550 --> 11:58.465
So you were unaware
of these pictures?

11:58.509 --> 12:00.729
Never seen them before?
- Correct.

12:00.772 --> 12:04.210
- Mm-hmm, I'm gonna give you a
mulligan on that one, Stewart.

12:04.254 --> 12:05.472
- Excuse me?

12:05.516 --> 12:07.518
- Bad idea to lie
to the police.

12:07.561 --> 12:10.129
- That's you, isn't it,
bangin' on Hoyt's front door?

12:10.173 --> 12:12.828
- Okay, I was...aware.

12:12.871 --> 12:15.526
A friend called, said there
were some photos circulating

12:15.569 --> 12:18.311
on some right-wing chat room.

12:18.355 --> 12:20.444
I flipped out.
I ran over to Hoyt's building.

12:20.487 --> 12:23.186
I wanted to talk to him--
no, you know what?

12:23.229 --> 12:25.362
I wanted to beat his ass
into the ground.

12:25.405 --> 12:26.755
But he wasn't home.

12:26.798 --> 12:29.235
- So you never got the chance
to confront him

12:29.279 --> 12:30.802
about these photos?
- No.

12:30.846 --> 12:33.674
I tried, trust me.
But he died.

12:33.718 --> 12:36.547
Got hit by a car.
- Bus.

12:36.590 --> 12:38.810
A bus someone pushed him
in front of.

12:38.854 --> 12:42.509
- You asking me if I--
- We are.

12:42.553 --> 12:44.947
- No, I didn't kill him.

12:46.426 --> 12:47.776
- You know who this girl is?

12:47.819 --> 12:49.821
- Yeah, that's Kimberly Ryan.

12:49.865 --> 12:51.518
She's on the same
basketball team

12:51.562 --> 12:54.304
as my daughter
and Hoyt's daughter.

12:54.347 --> 12:55.740
- That's definitely
my daughter,

12:55.784 --> 13:00.266
but she's never
been alone with Hoyt, ever.

13:00.310 --> 13:01.659
I'm not sure how he--

13:01.702 --> 13:03.922
- Maybe at a basketball game,
or a sleepover.

13:03.966 --> 13:07.230
- No, our kids
aren't really friends.

13:07.273 --> 13:09.798
Can I look
at those photos again?

13:11.930 --> 13:12.844
Yeah.

13:15.804 --> 13:19.024
My daughter's clothing
and her facial expressions,

13:19.068 --> 13:22.245
they match what's on
my wife's social media feed.

13:22.288 --> 13:24.813
Yeah, see?

13:24.856 --> 13:27.250
Same smile,
same clothes,

13:27.293 --> 13:29.556
same body angle.

13:29.600 --> 13:31.210
Someone photoshopped these.

13:31.254 --> 13:33.430
♪

13:33.473 --> 13:34.910
- Well,
the techs just confirmed

13:34.953 --> 13:36.389
the pictures are fake.

13:36.433 --> 13:38.043
- So Hoyt wasn't a pedophile?

13:38.087 --> 13:40.002
He was a victim
of an online smear campaign?

13:40.045 --> 13:41.438
- Ah, sure seems like that.

13:41.481 --> 13:42.874
- Hey, sorry to interrupt,

13:42.918 --> 13:44.702
but I'm scrolling through
this online forum

13:44.745 --> 13:46.225
where the photos of Hoyt
were circulating,

13:46.269 --> 13:47.792
and it is crazy.

13:47.836 --> 13:50.751
